commitResults.messageBody:
Modified the NameContainsKeywordsPredicate class to implement a fuzzy search that matches only contiguous substrings.

The isFuzzyMatch method was updated to keep track of the last matched index in both fullName and keyword. If the difference between the last matched index in fullName and the current matched index is greater than 1, then it indicates that the matched characters are not contiguous, and the method returns false.

Example: David Li will appear in Find Dav, vid, Li, Da, av, ID etc.

The NameContainsKeywordsPredicateTest class was modified to include additional test cases to test the new fuzzy search implementation.

commitResults.messageTitle: The new Session class provides a structured way to store a person's availability in the address book. The start and end date time are validated upon instantiation, ensuring that the start date time is before the end date time. The class also provides a convenient method to calculate the duration of the session. This commit also includes unit tests for the Session class

commitResults.messageBody:
To use the Session class, simply create a new instance with the appropriate start and end times. Example inputs are strings in the format "dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm". The class can then be used to compute the duration of the session.

The JSON format for storing Person objects has been modified to include a session field, which contains information about the session in the format "dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm to dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm".

Example: add n/John Doe p/98765432 a/311, Clementi Ave 2, #02-25 r/35 s/10-03-2022 10:00 to 10-03-2022 11:00 t/friends t/owesMoney

s/10-03-2022 10:00 to 10-03-2022 11:00

The UI has been updated to display session information for each Person in the main view. The PersonCard now includes a label for session start and end times, as well as the duration of the session.
